As used throughout this report, the terms overfishing and overfished are generally the same as defined for U.S. federal fisheries Â­ a rate or level of fishing mortality that jeopardizes the capacity of a fishery to produce the maximum sustainable yield on a continuing basis (Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act, Pub.
Law 94-265, 16 U.S.C.1801 Sec. 2).
With the exception of cancerous tumors infecting green sea turtles8 off the Main Hawaiian Islands, disease in the Pacific Islands is low to moderate.
