Runoff and sedimentation from coastal development have degraded coral reef ecosystems off southeastern Florida and the Keys, Puerto Rico, the USVI, most of the Main Hawaiian Islands, Guam, and the CNMI.
Runoff and sedimentation also occur in rural areas where forests have been removed for agriculture.
