the many coral diseases to emerge over the last 20 years, white-band disease is one of the most virulent, killing up to 90-95% of the elkhorn and staghorn corals off St. Croix, Puerto Rico, and southeastern Florida by the 1990s.
Near-shore reefs off high Pacific islands in American Samoa, the CNMI, and Palau experience runoff and sedimentation during tropical storms.
Although less widespread than overfishing, runoff and sedimentation are of considerable concern to managers in all jurisdictions.
