threatens reef structure and associated wildlife.
Groundings, anchor damage, and propellers speeding through shallow waterways are some of the most destructive chronic human factors (Fig. 6).
They cause significant localized damage to shallow-water coral reefs.
The increasing number of large ship and small boat groundings is a major threat off Florida, the USVI, and the Main Hawaiian Islands, and of moderate concern along other populated coasts.
